│ 2.  `%R0 = sub nsw i8 %L0, %L1`. The `nsw` flag means "no signed wrap". This guarantees that the signed subtraction does not overflow.                                                   │
│ 3.  `%RHS = icmp ult i8 %R0, -1`. In 8-bit two's complement, `-1` is `255` (or `0xFF`). So this is `icmp ult i8 %R0, 255`.                                                               │
│                                                                                                                                                                                          │
│ The simplification to `false` implies that the compiler believes `%R0` can never be less than `255` unsigned. This is equivalent to saying `%R0` must be `255`.                          │
│                                                                                                                                                                                          │
│ Let's examine the conditions:                                                                                                                                                            │
│ -   `samesign(%L0, %L1)`: Both are non-negative (sign bit 0) or both are negative (sign bit 1).                                                                                          │
│ -   `%L0 > %L1` (unsigned).                                                                                                                                                              │
│ -   `sub nsw i8 %L0, %L1` does not have signed overflow.                                                                                                                                 │
│                                                                                                                                                                                          │
│ The bug report provides a counterexample:                                                                                                                                                │
