│ -   `15 > 0` (unsigned) is true.                                                                                                                                                         │
│ -   `sub nsw i8 15, 0` is `15`, which is valid (no signed wrap).                                                                                                                         │
│ -   `%R0` is `15`.                                                                                                                                                                       │
│ -   `icmp ult i8 15, 255` is `true`.                                                                                                                                                     │
│                                                                                                                                                                                          │
│ The optimizer incorrectly simplifies this to `false`. This is a miscompilation.                                                                                                          │
│                                                                                                                                                                                          │
│ The simplification `icmp ult (sub nsw X, Y), C` is likely at fault. The `nsw` on the subtraction provides information about the operands `X` and `Y` and the result.                     │
