│ Let's analyze the `nsw` property on `sub`.                                                                                                                                               │
│ `sub nsw i8 %L0, %L1` means `sext(L0) - sext(L1)` does not overflow the signed `i8` range `[-128, 127]`.                                                                                 │
│                                                                                                                                                                                          │
│ The `samesign` property means:                                                                                                                                                           │
│ 1. `%L0 >= 0` and `%L1 >= 0` (signed)                                                                                                                                                    │
│ 2. `%L0 < 0` and `%L1 < 0` (signed)                                                                                                                                                      │
