│ `llvm/test/Analysis/ValueTracking/implied-condition-samesign.ll`. This file name is a huge clue. It suggests the simplification is happening via `ValueTracking`'s `isImpliedCondition`  │
│ logic, which `instsimplify` can use to reason about conditions that are known to be true based on dominating branches.                                                                   │
│                                                                                                                                                                                          │
│ The reproducer has a branch on `%LHS = icmp samesign ugt i8 %L0, %L1`. In the `LHS_true` block, `instsimplify` can assume this condition is true. The miscompilation happens inside this │
